 only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":15,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Farrington, Knight was born in 1440, in Worden Hall, Lancashire, England, his father, William Farington II, was 25 and his mother, Lady Margaret Halsall, was 19. He had at least 2 daughters with Lady Alice Ashton. He died in 1501, in Farington, Lancashire, England, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1440–1501":"1440–1501","1439–1482":"1439–1482","1441–Female":"1441–Surnud","1444–1501":"1444–1501","1430–1485":"1430–1485","1465–1510":"1465–1510","1475–1510":"1475–1510","1415–1456":"1415–1456","1421–1448":"1421–1448","1440":"1440","Abt 1456":"umbes 1456","1482":"1482","1448":"1448","1415":"1415","1501":"1501","1456":"1456","1455":"1455","1510":"1510","1444":"1444","1465":"1465","Abt 1475":"umbes 1475","1443":"1443","1421":"1421","Abt 1485":"umbes 1485","1475":"1475","1485":"1485","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1439":"1439","Leyland, Lancashire, England":"Leyland, Lancashire, England","Farrington, Lancashire, England":"Farington, Lancashire, England","Worden Hall, Lancashire, England":"Worden Hall, Lancashire, England","Farington, Lancashire, England":"Farington, Lancashire, England","Farrington, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Farington, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancas